        "subject": "LU-19399 utils: Fix NULL check in copy_file_expandable()",
        "message": "LU-19399 utils: Fix NULL check in copy_file_expandable()\n\nThis patch fixes a NULL check after calloc that was checking for the\nwrong pointer, which can cause invalid pointer faults under memory\npressure.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial testlist=sanity-sec\nSigned-off-by: Marc Vef <mvef@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: I7ffca4a897cc5e8cfcbe51d249e55770fda9b1aa\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/61385\nReviewed-by: Sebastien Buisson <sbuisson@ddn.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <green@whamcloud.com>\nTested-by: Maloo <maloo@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: James Simmons <jsimmons@infradead.org>\nTested-by: jenkins <devops@whamcloud.com>\n"
      },
